SIMPLE: infralapsarian
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Infralapsarian
<hw>In`fra*lap*sa"ri*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Infra</ets> + <ets>lapse</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>infralapsaire.</ets> See <er>Lapse</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Eccl.
Hist.)</fld> <def>One of that class of Calvinists who consider the
decree of election as contemplating the apostasy as past and the elect
as being at the time of election in a fallen and guilty state; --
opposed to <contr>Supralapsarian</contr>. The former considered the
election of grace as a remedy for an existing evil; the latter regarded
the fall as a part of God's original purpose in regard to men.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Infralapsarian</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Infralapsarian
<hw>In`fra*lap*sa"ri*an</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Theol.)</fld> <def>Of
or pertaining to the Infralapsarians, or to their doctrine.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Infralapsarianism</ent>⟦br⟧
